    "description": "Discipline: Waijia\nSkill: Athletics Against Attack Roll\nType: Counter\nQi: 1\n\nYou bend back to evade a Melee Attack, nearly touching the ground with your head then springing back with force to strike your foe. If anyone attacks you with a Melee Attack you can use this counter. On a success you bend back and avoid the strike, then swiftly bounce back to deliver a potent blow of your own (mundane strike but at a +1d10 Damage bonus per Rank of Waijia). This does not work against characters with Qi levels higher than you. The user must be inebriated by alcohol to use this Technique. Cathartic: When used Cathartically your Damage roll is Open.",
